  "texts": [
    "We call this theory the \"machine bias\" hypothesis, according to which LLM errors do not stem from imbalanced training data.",
    "The article proceeds as follows.",
    "We first review the existing empirical work that uses LLMs to replicate human subjects, both in the human and social sciences and in computer science.",
    "We especially show that some empirical elements in favor of the machine bias hypothesis have been found in previous studies, but that they were not fully theorized.",
    "Second, we describe the experiment we designed to adjudicate between the three hypotheses, based on a \"silicon sampling\" task, asking several survey questions to a language model."
  ],
